Help [=[

stat.dexp(x [, r])
stat.pexp(x [, r])
stat.qexp(p [, r])
------------------

Computes the density (`dexp`), cumulative distribution function (`pexp`),
and inverse cdf (`qexp`) for the *exponential* distribution with rate `r`.
The default value for `r` is one. The exponential distribution has density
`r * exp(-r * x)`.
]=]
